(n) a tense used to express action that is on-going at the time of utterance
Synonyms: present progressive

>>> perfective tense

(n) a tense of verbs used in describing action that has been completed (sometimes regarded as perfective aspect)
Synonyms: perfect

>>> perfect tense

(n) verb form that indicates that an action or circumstance occurred earlier than the time under consideration, often focusing attention on the resulting state rather than on the occurrence itself
Synonyms: perfect

>>> present perfect

(n) a perfective tense used to express action completed in the present
Synonyms: present perfect tense
